<p><a href="http://philosophy.columbia.edu/node/206" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Philip Kitcher</a>, professor emeritus of philosophy at Columbia University, has been named the winner of the Frontiers of Knowledge Prize in the Humanities by the Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria (BBVA) Foundation.<span id="more-53366"></span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="alignnone  wp-image-53369 aligncenter" src="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/kitcher-philip-2.png" alt="" width="620" height="450" srcset="https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/kitcher-philip-2.png 750w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/kitcher-philip-2-300x218.png 300w, https://dailynous.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/kitcher-philip-2-400x290.png 400w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px" /></p>
<p>The €400,000 (approximately $438,000) prize was awarded to Professor Kitcher for his &#8220;trailblazing work [which] addresses a broad spectrum of the core questions of our time.&#8221;</p>
<p>According to the prize announcement, prize committee chair John Dupré (Exeter) says:</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;"><em>What stands out in Kitcher’s work is its enormous breadth, the way its spans the philosophy of science (to improve the practice of scientific research), ethics, politics and education, interrelating all these domains in order to improve society and further its progress.</em></p>
<p>The <a href="https://www.frontiersofknowledgeawards-fbbva.es/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Frontiers of Knowledge Prizes</a> are awarded annually in the humanities and several other areas.</p>
<p>The full prize announcement is <a href="https://www.frontiersofknowledgeawards-fbbva.es/noticias/the-frontiers-of-knowledge-award-goes-to-philip-kitcher-a-humanistic-intellectual-whose-philosophical-output-has-addressed-a-broad-spectrum-of-the-core-questions-of-our-time/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>. A list of previous winners is <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BBVA_Foundation_Frontiers_of_Knowledge_Award#Laureates" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>.</p><p>The post <a href="https://dailynous.com/2025/04/08/kitcher-wins-frontiers-of-knowledge-prize/">Kitcher Wins Frontiers of Knowledge Prize</a> first appeared on <a href="https://dailynous.com">Daily Nous</a>.</p>